Description.0: GraphQL API for WordPress is an open source plugin for WordPress, to install a GraphQL server. This plugin enables developers to bring a GraphQL experience into a WordPress site. Features: Advanced architecture. Forward-looking. Versatile and powerful. It requires WordPress 5.4 or above, PHP 7.4+ for development and PHP 7.1+ for production. It was created by developer Leonardo Losoviz.
Description.1: DHTMLX offers a variety of JavaScript UI components and libraries that enable web developers to build advanced web apps and accelerate the whole development process. The portfolio of DHTMLX products includes the following: popular components for project management apps such as Gantt and Scheduler, Suite with 20+UI widgets, Diagram library for well-structured and clear data visualization, Vault tool for convenient file uploading, web-based Spreadsheet solution, Rich text editor, and Pivot component for handling large datasets. All DHTMLX libraries are notable for comprehensive API, enhanced customization capabilities, compatibility with popular JS frameworks and client-side technologies, support of modern browsers and lack of external dependencies.
Description.2: Mocki allows developers to create and setup mock APIs with simulated responses, delays, and generated test data. The API is automatically deployed as the configuration is pushed to GitHub. The latest version is 0.1.4.
Description.3: Reddit.NET is a .NET Standard managed library that provides easy access to the Reddit API with virtually no boilerplate code required.
Description.4: The UNICORN Binance WebSocket Library analyzes data, produces web streams, and offers asynchronous streams. Installation and upgrade available.
Description.5: This Postlight library is a Mercury Parser to extract data from any URL for; article content, titles, authors, published dates, excerpts, lead images, and more. The Postlight Mercury Parser provides a way to create custom parsers using simple JavaScript and CSS selectors and allows you to manage parsing and migration edge cases. The Mercury Web Parser API is shut down, so if your application or product is actively using the Mercury Web Parser API, it is recommended that you transition to your own hosted version of Mercury. The Mercury Parser code is now free and open-source, including this code for the Mercury Parser API. You can use the library to deploy an instance of the API to your own AWS account.
Description.6: Super Graph creates GraphQL APIs for Rails applications. Written in Go, this library builds high performance servers that are easy to deploy. This implementation automatically learns the desired database's structure and relationships. Super Graph offers built-in JSON Web Tokens support, and Rails authentication.
Description.7: Webix is an enterprise JavaScript Library for cross-platform app development with HTML5 JavaScript widgets, UI controls and material skins. Our library consist of 99+ UI widgets and feature-rich CSS / HTML5 JavaScript controls. Also, you will get number of responsive material skin designs to speed up your web development.
Description.8: DeviceHub JavaScript Library for React JavaScript Framework provides a JavaScript platform for building user interfaces.
Description.9: The OpenPrescribing Python Library for Django Python Framework provides the OpenPrescribingAPI alongside the dashboards of the GP prescribing data for the HSCIC.
Description.10: The Bol.com C# Library for .NET Framework provides the Bol.com Open API for building ecommerce apps. The Library is written in C#. Its deployment requires .NET Framework 4.5 and JSON.NET 5.0.6.
Description.11: The FilePond JavaScript Library for Angular JavaScript Framework provides the Filepond platform for integration in a developer’s project. The library is crucial for exposing the Filepond public API which is useful for manipulating Filepond instances on the page.
Description.12: FilePond JavaScript Library for jQuery Framework provides the Filepond platform for integration in a developer’s project. The library is crucial for exposing the Filepond public API which is useful for manipulating Filepond instances on the page.
Description.13: The Buefy JavaScript Library for VueJS JavaScript Framework is a lightweight library of responsive UI components for the VueJS platform. The VueJS framework is more or less a clone of the Bulma framework.
Description.14: The PRX CMS Ruby Library for Ruby on Rails Framework provides the CMS API. The library follows PRX’s standards for developing applications using the CMS API. Its consumption also requires various integrations and dependencies including mysql and memcached. The library is currently a beta release.
Description.15: The Soapforce Ruby Gem Library by Octiv s a Savon-based wrapper for the Salesforce.com API. The gem operates on Savon 2 and its current version is 0.2.1.
Description.16: This .Net Library is a custom CruiseControl.NET plugin which will post build results to a Campfire chatroom. Campfire utilizes vanilla XML/JSON over HTTP and returns Account, Rooms, Search, Messages and more. Campfire is like instant messaging, but designed exclusively for groups and allows you to save transcripts, share text, files, and code in real time.
Description.17: The Github PHP Library by Kdyby for Nette Framework provides access to Github API’s development tools. Its deployment requires the onwards of PHP 5.3.2 with cURL extension enabled.
Description.18: The Atlassian Connect Haskell Library for Snap Framework by Atlassian provides the Atlassian API integrations for building apps on the Snap Framework.
Description.19: The Freezer Python Library connects an application with a disaster recovery platform provided by OpenStack. The current version is 5.0.0.
Description.20: The Github PHP Library for Joomla Framework provides access to the Github API. Its documentation provides paths for instantiating Github and accessing its developer tools.
Description.21: The Github PHP Library by Graham Campbell for Laravel Framework provides the Github API via the Laravel platform. The library’s consumption requires the onwards of PHP 7 and its support is restrcited to Laravel 5.1 to 5.5.
Description.22: The Bitmovin Player Ruby Library for Rails Framework provides the Bitmovin Player API. It is essentially an adaptive HTML5Video Playerfor Rails. Current version is 1.0.1.
Description.23: The Apigility ZF RPC PHP Library helps implementing RPC web services in Zend Framework. Some features include: defining controllers as PHP callables and creating a whitelist of HTTP request methods. The library can be used with Apigility to provide an object model of all captured documentation information and provides a configurable MVC endpoint for returning documentation. Apigility offers JSON representations that can be parsed and used in any mobile framework and allows you to write for the web or native applications simultaneously.
Description.24: The Apigility PHP Library assists in the creation of APIs using agile methodologies. It is available in JSON architecture in RESTful format, using OAuth2 and HTTP to authenticate. Agility can be downloaded in any Linux, PC, Apple, or PHP related computing system.
Description.25: Nozzle Animate CSS Library for AngularJS Framework provides the AnimateCSS’s regular functionality for implementing animation concepts.
Description.26: Fastify is a fast and low overhead web framework for NodeJS. The Fastify React JavaScript Library for NextJS Framework provides JavaScript tools for interacting with the Fastify platform.
Description.27: Cloudinary is a web asset management platform that allows users to store and manage their digital and web assets in the cloud. The Cloudinary JavaScript Library for jQuery Framework provides the Cloudinary API when building apps on the JavaScript language platform. It is designed to integrate seamlessly with your existing jQuery apps.
Description.28: Cloudinary is a web asset management platform that allows users to store and manage their digital and web assets in the cloud. The Cloudinary Ruby Library for Ruby on Rails Framework provides the Cloudinary API when building apps on the Ruby language platform. It is designed to integrate seamlessly with your existing Gem apps.
Description.29: Cloudinary is a web asset management platform that allows users to store and manage their digital and web assets in the cloud. The Cloudinary Python Library for Django Framework provides the Cloudinary API when building apps on the Python language platform. It is designed to integrate seamlessly with your existing Python apps.

The Cloudinary React JavaScript Library for React Framework provides the Cloudinary API when building apps on the JavaScript language platform. It is designed to integrate seamlessly with your existing React apps.
Description.31: The Atlassian Connect Express NodeJS Library for Express Framework by Atlassian provides the HipChat API integrations for building apps on the Express Framework for NodeJS. Documentation provides a tutorial for consuming the library.
Description.32: The Hipchat Python Library for Flask Framework by Atlassian provides API integrations for building HipChat Connect add-ons on the Flask Framework. Documentation provides a tutorial for consuming the library.
Description.33: The Hipchat NodeJS Library for KoaJS Framework by Atlassian provides the HipChat API integrations for building apps on the Koa web framework. Documentation provides a tutorial for consuming the library.
Description.34: The ZfrPusher PHP Library for Zend Framework provides the Pusher HTTP API when building messaging applications. Its deployment requires the onwards of Guzzle Library 3.5 dependency. Documentation provides integration and framework integration procedures.
Description.35: The Ably PHP Library for Laravel Framework by Ably is designed to provide access to the Ably API through the Laravel framework for PHP. The library actually provides a Façade alongside an injectable AblyService that serve as development tools for a singleton Ably instance. Its documentation provides Ably’s installation and configuration paths.
Description.36: The Pusher PHP Library for Yii Framework allows developers to access the Pusher API when building messaging apps. The library must be tested on Yii 1.1.10 during deployment.
Description.37: The TuneIt Android Library by Nikhil Chaudhari generates the PCM tones of octave for an Android phone. Sample application code is available on GitHub.
Description.38: The Antideo PHP Library by Antideo allows querying Antideo's REST API. Developers can get email address info, get IP address WHOIS info and category, get IP address health details, and get IP address location.
Description.39: The Kueri.me API Library by Kueri.me is available in JavaScript language to integrate a search-box complete. It can display natural language responses in a table as SQL.
Description.40: The Enrichr Python Library by Stephen Newhouse allows developers to integrate the Enrichr API into their Python applications. This SDK has been tested with Python 2.7.11.
Description.41: The Whatsapp PHP Chat API Library by Martin Wagner allows developers to access Whatsapp using the Chat-API library written in PHP. This SDK stands up an RPC-style API that lets users send and receive Whatsapp messages using almost any language.
Description.42: The ConnectWise PHP SDK by Brian Buller integrates business management features via API interaction. It allows connection with CodeIgniter Library and PHP Class.
Description.43: This library is a wrapper around the SparkPost API and includes documentation and examples.
Description.44: This library is a wrapper around the SparkPost API and includes documentation and examples.
Description.45: This library is a wrapper around the SparkPost API and includes documentation and examples.
Description.46: This library is a wrapper around the SparkPost API and includes documentation and examples.
Description.47: The Plivo Python SDK by Close.io allows developers to integrate the Plivo API into their Python applications. Example code is included in the documentation.
Description.48: The WealthEngine Node.js SDK by Zack Proser calls the WealthEngine REST API which provides a net worth platform for sales and fundraising to integrate with existing applications. This asynchronous wrapper supports the 4 currently public endpoints.
Description.49: The Rally .NET SDK by Joshua Stupplebeen interacts with the API, even though Rally Software does not maintain the kit actively. User guide provides links to access REST API and Web Services documentation. For support, ask a question at http://stackoverflow.com/questions/ask?tags=rally
Description.50: The Yummly Python SDK by Derrick Gilland interacts with the API but it is not officially affiliated with Yummy. To implement food recommendation features into applications, developers can install via pip and create a client object. As initial parameters, the client takes API Id, API Key, and Timeout. See resources to search and obtain recipes from the API.
Description.51: The Runscope Ruby SDK by Chris Warren calls the Runscope API that provides developers with a testing system and monitoring for APIs. Performance and usage metrics can be accessed as well. Developers need to set up a Runscope account; it returns JSON data, and requires an OAuth2 token.
Description.52: The Yahoo Fantasy Sports .NET Wrapper by maradonario is a .NET Web Services wrapper for the Yahoo Fantasy Sports API. Yahoo Fantasy Sports is the world's largest fantasy sports provider, allowing users to compete against each other using statistics from real-world competitions. The Yahoo Fantasy Sports API provides rich data on leagues, teams and player information.
Description.53:
The Telegram Bot Ruby SDK by SuHun Han is a Ruby wrapper that communicates with the Telegram-CLI.
The Telegram Bot API provides services that can integrate bots with AI applications in mind (this includes teaching, broadcasting, and connecting features into software components).
Description.54: The Chargify Ruby SDK by Chargify contains installation and usage to interact with the API and implement into an application. Includes available configuration options, duplicate prevention, and Rails compatibility. By Eric Farkas.
Description.55: With the API.AI Python library by API.AI, users can read and write applications associated to natural language processing, machine learning, and voice recognition. Authored by Dmitriy Kuragin, resources include running examples, installation, and documentation. To start implementation, create an account at http://api.ai/
Description.56: The CrunchBase R library by tarakc02 helps developers to integrate data for statistics and graphical displays purposes. Opportunities of development include data related to organizations, people, and products. An API Key is needed to start. Learn more about the documentation at http://data.crunchbase.com/docs
Description.57: The CrunchBase PHP library by Juancho Rossi explains how to use this resource with a few lines of code. Considering the implementation of applications working in PHP language, developers can access organizations, people, and products, the 3 main items in the CrunchBase dataset. Documentation available at https://developer.crunchbase.com/docs
Description.58: The Google Analytics Management Python library by Google aims to call Google APIs in a simple way and handle auth with fewer lines of code. Developers can use this library with Google App Engine or with custom installation. Considering additional projects, the Python library is also compatible with more APIs. To find out which one works with a specific project, visit https://developers.google.com/api-client-library/python/apis/
Description.59: The Google Analytics Management PHP library by Google in beta stage is available to facilitate the interaction with the API. To get started, developers install the library. Next, they authenticate and authorize choosing from API Keys, OAuth 2.0 for web server, and OAuth 2.0 for server-to-server. In the same site, learn how to send batch requests, upload media, use pagination, and migrate from 0.6.x
Description.60: Google provides the Analytics Management Objective-C library to access JSON APIs. Developers need iOS 3 and Mac OS X 10.5. The introduction to this library explains how to add the library to a project, add custom data, and use the API without generated classes. In the link to the demos, users can find samples with Blogger, Books, Calendar, Drive, and Storage.
Description.61: Google Analytics Management has released a JavaScript library in beta stage. The site contains 2 main topics: How to make an API request using the JavaScript library and how it looks in JavaScript. Additional resources guide users to get a Google account, choose Google services, and get access Keys for a new application.
Description.62: The Yahoo BOSS API provides sets of data to create customized search engines and innovative user experiences. This Yahoo BOSS Ruby library created by Tobias Begalke contains configuration and parameters. Within parameters, developers can find image search service, news search service, blog search service, spelling service, and related service. For more information, check the BOSS API guide at https://developer.yahoo.com/boss/search/boss_api_guide/
Description.63: Brewery DB was created for developers to developers to access references of regional breweries, beer style guide, brewers guilds, and Brewery DB Apps. The SDK aims to integrate the API services of craft beer search in Python language, once users register for an Api Key and wrap all GET requests of the documentation.
Description.64: The New York Times Article Search Ruby SDK by Kazuhiro Yamada offers interaction with the functionalities of search, reference, and news service of the New York Times from 1851 to the present time. Includes installation, usage, and contribution steps. Additional API information is available at http://developer.nytimes.com/docs/read/article_search_api_v2%3E%60_
Description.65: The New York Times Article Search Python SDK by Evan Sherlock offers pip installation and pypi dependencies to import and initialize with the Api Key. The Article Search API offers search and reference of the New York Times' articles from September 18, 1851 until today's date. API additional information available at http://developer.nytimes.com/docs/read/article_search_api_v2%3E%60_
Description.66: Google Fusion Tables is an experimental app that offers a Java library to interact with the REST API. The aim is to avoid the creation of HTTP requests and the parsing of responses. Highlights include calls to the API, OAuth 2.0 authentication, and Google App Engine support. Created to run on Android 1.5+.
Description.67: The official Google Custom Search library in Java language allows API integration to build customized search engines in websites, blogs, and groups of websites. Resources available include examples to make calls, authenticate, upload media, download media, and work with Google App Engine. To specify, this Java library in beta stage runs on Android 1.5+.
Description.68: The Zacks Data R Library by Quandl offers interaction with API data related to financial analysis, earnings, and estimate trends. References on GitHub include installation using development tools and CRAN package. Contains authentication with Api Key and usage with graphing data example. Authored by RaymondMcT.
Description.69: The Google Shopping Content Objective-C Library by Google can access API data to sell products on Google, list ads, drive traffic, and increase sales. Developers can interact with the JSON API, working with iOS 3+ and Mac OS X 10.5+. Available introduction and example applications.
Description.70: The Bing Translator Python Library by Will Filho is a Python library that gives developers tools to work with the Translator API. Some of the features are performing single translations, multiple translations and listening to the pronunciation of a certain word or phrase.
Description.71: The MusicBrainz (gomusicbrainz) Golang Library by Michael Wendland is a Go (Golang) WS2 Client Library for use with MusicBrainz. GoMusicBrainz provides developers methods to perform search and lookup requests. The MusicBrainz database contains a huge amount of music metadata, which is maintained by the MusicBrainz community.
Description.72: Perfect Money is a financial option for Internet businesses that intend to receive and transfer funds online. A library available in .NET language can help to interact with the API functionalities of checking accounts, exchanging rates, and creating e-Vouchers. Perfect Money additionally offers plugins for shop-carts such as Drupal, Wordpress, and UberCart.
Description.73: This JSON server helps to get a fake REST API in less than 30 seconds without any coding. It aims to accelerate back-end to prototype and mock projects. Available examples, routes, and deployment. Additional remote schema, JavaScript file support, and module.

Description.139: The MusicBrainz (libmusicbrainz-objc) Objective-C Library by Joachim Brandon LeBlanc is an iOS Library for the MusicBrainz Web Service. The MusicBrainz database contains a huge amount of music metadata, which is maintained by the MusicBrainz community.
Description.140: The SoundCloud Java library created by Darius Morawiec aims to simplify the access to the API capabilities of sounds, users, and sets. Resources include dependencies, usage with API, REST, GET, PUT, POST, and DELETE, examples, and processing. The author suggests that the service of Apigee is optimum to learn and test the official SoundCloud API.
Description.141: This library in Java language for the Spotify Echo Nest API provides access to the Track Analysis API. With this resource, developers can obtain track's loudness, mode, key, tempo, signature, detailed beat structure, harmonic content, and timbre information. See examples with hottest songs, static playlists, and similar artists at https://github.com/echonest/jEN/tree/master/src/com/echonest/api/v4/examples
Description.142: The Spotify Echo Nest Objective-C library access the music functionalities of the API with Apple development in mind. Resources include full access to artists, songs, playlists, and taste profiles methods. It also provides methods to retrieve information of a particular track. An example app is available to demonstrate how to integrate the library into an XCode project.
Description.143: Official Spotify Echo Nest Python library created to access music search, recommendations, and remix tools. This is an open source project that interacts the API methods of artist, song, and track. Includes installation, a getting started guide, and examples.
Description.144: The Routific Ruby Library by Routific allows developers to integrate the Routific API into their Ruby applications. Usage examples are included in the documentation.
Description.145: The Routific Node.js Library by Routific allows developers to integrate the Routific API into their Node.js applications. Code examples are included in the documentation.
Description.146: The Withings PHP library by Alexander Liljengård was written with the purpose to adapt to the body metrics' functionalities of the API. It works with OAuth1 to get measures of activity, body, intraday, and sleep. For more information about authorization, parameters, and reference, visit http://oauth.withings.com/api
Description.147: Cryptsy provides bitcoin and digital currency exchange services through its API. The Cryptsy PHP library by Ronald A. Richardson can be used mainly for DogeCoin and BitCoin. Contact the author for more information theprestig3@gmail.com
Description.148: Cryptsy offers bitcoin and digital currency trading services. The Cryptsy Node.js library created by Ek Palmer contains an illustrated example to demonstrate a list of all markets that participate in trade events. What the API does for users is to allow the query of general market data and orderbook data. Additional information such as market data, transactions, and execution of trades is available with authenticated methods.
Description.149: The Trakt.tv PHP Library by Bram Wubs allows developers to integrate version 2 of the Trakt.tv API into their PHP applications.
Description.150: Use this python library to interact with Instagram's photo sharing API. The unofficial library is authored by Boris Shifrin and is offered under a BSD license.
Description.151: The SolidShops PHP Library by SolidShops allows developers to integrate the SolidShops API into their PHP applications. Code examples are provided for all of the library's methods.
Description.152: The Clarifai Python Library by Clarifai allows developers to integrate the Clarifai API into their Python applications. Usage examples are provided in the documentation.
Description.153: The Clarifai Java Library by Clarifai allows developers to integrate the Clarifai API's methods into their Java applications. This library requires JDK 1.6+.
Description.154: TinEye offers reverse search image. It works by providing an image to display where the image is on the web. Useful for brand's presence and person's influence. This is a TinEye Node.js library shared by collaborator Andrew Sliwinski. It contains installation, basic use, and testing. Andrew is the co-founder of DIY.org and the director of learning products at Mozilla Foundation. Reach andrewsliwinski@acm.org
Description.155: Walk Score aims to create walking communities by matching living spaces with close amenities. The purpose of this Python library created by Peter Hornyack is to get familiar with the API capacities that include to display properties and to search apartments. In addition to API access, developers can consider to mash up walking scores like the ones that require building permits. Dependencies available at https://github.com/pjh/pyutils
Description.156: The 500px Ruby wrapper by Chris Micacchi has been designed to interact easily with the API capabilities of search, retrieve, and upload photos. It aims to reuse HTTP connections. 500px is a community of photographers who can showcase their projects, discover new photography styles, and find royalty-free art.
Description.157: Basecamp offers project management tools to collaborate and communicate. The Basecamp PHP library created by Netvlies contains authorization with OAuth, API calls, and identification. It aims to facilitate project management with assigned projects, to-do lists, and active projects.
Description.158: The LiveChat Ruby library shared as a repository by Alexandre Maia, contains the necessary elements to interact with the API such as installation and connection. An additional element includes a list of methods like agents, canned responses, chats, goals, groups, reports, status, and visitors. Under MIT license. Developers are invited to contribute to the project. For more info, contact developer alexandre.maia@gmail.com
Description.159: The LiveChat Node.js library developed by Grzegorz Wyszyński contains lines of code for installation and a quick start. API methods include agents, canned responses, chats, goals, groups, reports, status, and visitors. LiveChat helps sales representatives to interact with customers with the aim to provide an efficient service. More of the API available at http://developers.livechatinc.com/rest-api/#add-custom-visitor-details
Description.160: This is a PHP library with ready-to-use LiveChat API implementation created by Grzegorz Wyszyński. LiveChat provides chat services to help customers who visit websites. Include ratings to improve the quality of the interaction. One of the main benefits of this tool is to dissipate any concern clients might have in order to increase sales.
Description.161: This is a Node.js wrapper for the GovTrack data API created by Mark Guerra. It contains guides to add bill, co-sponsorship, person, role, and voters features into applications. Initially, GovTrack was created by Joshua Tauberer with the goal to offer open access to parliamentary tracking at no cost.
Description.162: The Optimizely Python Library by Optimizely allows developers to integrate the Optimizely API into their Python applications. Example uses are included in the documentation.
Description.163: The Optimizely Command Line Interface Library by FunnelEnvy allows developers to access the Optimizely API from the Command Line Interface. This library uses Node.js
Description.164: The Optimizely Node.js Library by FunnelEnvy allows developers to integrate the Optimizely API into their Node.js applications. This library is offered under the Apache 2.0 License.

Description.166: The Optimizely Ruby Library by Martijn Scheijbeler is an unofficial gem that allows developers to integrate the Optimizely API into their Ruby applications.
Description.167: CheapShark is about digital game deals. The API data affords to integrate pricing features into website and applications. With simplicity in mind, developer Antonio Gurgel created this library in Ruby language, which includes installation and usage. For more information, visit http://www.cheapshark.com/api/
Description.168:
TomTom WEBFLEET.connect is a software-as-a-service fleet management system. Resources in the official website include an SDK, code samples, and a PERL library. This library demonstrates how to import addresses into WEBFLEET, query for objects, replicate messages to a database, create a file to show a track with Google Earth, and generate an RSS feed. Available in the file
WEBFLEET-Connect-1.27.zip
Description.169: The Optimizely JavaScript Library by Optimizely allows developer to integrate the Optimizely API into their web pages via JavaScript code.
Description.170: The Vbout PHP Library by Vbout allows developers to integrate the Vbout API into their PHP applications. A code example is included in the documentation.
Description.171: With Rome2Rio, users can discover how to arrive to any place in the world by plane, train, bus, ferry, and automobile. The Rome2Rio Ruby library by Alex Beregszaszi allows to interact with the API features that include point to point search, multi-hop planning, global coverage, and geo-coder technology just like the functionalities that can be seen in the Rome2Rio website. The author created this project for Soundtravel, a website that plans an entire travel itinerary to follow favorite world concerts. More at http://soundtravel.co/
Description.172: Exact Online is an accounting software that aims to improve the efficiency of businesses in real time. The Exact Online Python library by Walter Doekes aims to facilitate the interaction with the REST API. Contains usage, set up links, and resources. Further reading includes links to the API, a guide to create credentials, and Exact Online tips by author Bas van Beek, useful to get more use of the API.
Description.173: The Microsoft Translator Python Library by Openlabs allows developers to integrate the Microsoft Translator API into their Python applications. This library is offered under the BSD license.
Description.174: The MindBody Ruby Library by Stafford Brunk allows developers to integrate the MindBody API v0.5 into their Ruby applications.
Description.175: The 7digital Java Library by 7digital allows developers to integrate the 7digital API's methods into their Java applications.

To start using the library, study the examples for web applications, service applications, and installed applications. Additional to Analytics Management, this .NET library can be used to interact with more APIs. Choose from an extended list at https://developers.google.com/api-client-library/dotnet/apis/
Description.177: Google Analytics Core Reporting library available in Java language. The Core Reporting API is known as an instrument to access report data in Google Analytics. Developers can build custom dashboards, save time with complex tasks, and integrate Google Analytics to other apps. In particular cases, Google suggests to use the Analytics Management API to access configuration data in order to work with profile information.
Description.178: The DocuSign Node.js library by DocuSign aims to simplify the interaction with the API. It uses DocuSign SDK and Database.com to obtain electronic signatures from tax documents, send updated to the finance department, and update the member in the database. Authored by Jeff Douglas on GitHub.

Description.187: The MusicBrainz (libmusicbrainz) C/C++ Library by MusicBrainz is a client library for developers. The MusicBrainz database contains a huge amount of music metadata, which is maintained by the MusicBrainz community.
Description.188: The MusicBrainz C/C++ Library by MusicBrainz is a client cover art archive library for developers. Using this library, developers can add cover art capabilities to their applications. The MusicBrainz database contains a huge amount of music metadata, which is maintained by the MusicBrainz community.
Description.189: The MusicBrainz C Library by MusicBrainz is a client library to assist developers in creating MusicBrainz disc IDs and freedbs from audio CDs. The MusicBrainz database contains a huge amount of music metadata, which is maintained by the MusicBrainz community.
Description.190: The MusicBrainz Python Library by MusicBrainz is a client library for developers to get easier access to the MusicBrainz database using the XML web service. The MusicBrainz database contains a huge amount of music metadata, which is maintained by the MusicBrainz community.
Description.191: This Marvel Comics Android library by Trey Robinson offers access to the API features which allow to build websites and applications with Marvel data. The RESTful API displays JSON responses associated with Marvel's stories, characters, and individual comic issues.
Description.192: The Beats Music Python library by Teja Vishwanadha allows developers to work with two interfaces: the API object and the suite of models. The API object refers to a wrapper and models specify user friendly interactions. Easy for the user, somehow more complex for the developer, according to the author. The functionality of the API affords to access data related to music catalogs, music tracks, and music playlists.
Description.193: What the Node.js library for Beats Music does for a developer is to authenticate into an application or framework that supports Connect-style middleware. It is named Passport-Beatsmusic by Mark Purugganan. This passport is a strategy to authenticate using OAuth 2.0 API. Resources of this project include line of code for installation and instructions to configure and authenticate requests.
Description.194: The USA Today Ruby library can access the Census API data with an API key. Features of this API include ethnicity, housing, population, and race from the 2000 and 2010 US census. USA Today API displays results of news articles since 2004 in XML and JSON formats. This wrapper can be found on the official USA Today site, and it was authored by author Derek Willis on GitHub.
Description.195: The USA Today YQL library by USA Today uses Yahoo Query Language to access the Articles API. With this resource, developers can access data from top news, search query, reporter, sections, and time range. In detail, Articles API can retrieve editorial content, use tag search, and call feeds for one of the USA Today communities. For more information, contact author Sebastian Spier blog@airness.de
Description.196: The 7digital C# Library by 7digital allows developers to access the 7digital API from their C# applications. The latest version of this library requires .Net version 4.5.0+.
Description.197: The 7digital Node.js Library by 7digital allows developers to integrate the 7digital API into their Node.js application. It will return responses parsed as JavaScript objects.
Description.198: The 7digital Python Library by 7digital allows developers to integrate the 7digital API into their Python applications. Usage examples are provided in the documentation.
Description.199: The Twilio Erlang Library by Ryan Huffman is an Erlang library that was developed to communicate with TwiML and the Twilio API. Developers can use it in a traditional module usage or in extended TwiML. Twilio provides a simple hosted API and markup language for businesses to quickly build scalable, reliable and advanced voice and SMS communications applications.
Description.200: The Google Webmaster Tools .NET library by Google is available to download. The site contains links to browse the .NET reference documentation, access the developer's guide, and interact with the API. This library could be beneficial to use the search console, a service part of Webmaster Tools. The console monitors sites' performance in Google search results.
Description.201: Google Webmaster tools is a service that monitors and maintains a web presence in Google Search results. This is the official Python library that contains requirements and installation. The App engine, also included, serves to add an application like a third party. More information about Webmaster tools available at https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/4559176?hl=en
Description.202: NOAA National Weather Service alerts, predicts, and forecasts climate changes in the United States. This is a Ruby client library for NOAA created by developer Andrew M. Whalen. It contains data to interact with forecast and current weather conditions.
Description.203: Open Weather Map is a service that provides weather information with interactive graphics. The Open Weather Map .NET library by Joan Caron is an asynchronous project that interacts with the API. In the official site, users can review the API features that include current weather data, historical data, weather station network, weather forecast, map layers, and data from weather stations. Temperature shows Celsius degrees.
Description.204: The Walmart Ruby library is open to work with the Products Search API. Users who want to access this API, need to register for a Walmart Open account to obtain a key. API calls can be made from an interactive API tool. Documentation available at https://developer.walmartlabs.com/docs
Description.205:
The official Walmart Java library is open to interact with the Product Lookup API and the Search Lookup API.
Developers can download the source code, download the jar with dependencies, and access the java doc on GitHub. Sample code in Java language demonstrates how to work with special buy categories, fetch price information, and search results with keywords.
Description.206: Google Maps Elevation displays data on the surface of the earth and under depth locations of the ocean floor. Libraries in JavaScript provide code and examples to draw with tools, navigate with functions, and encode with methods.
Description.207: The Yahoo Search Python library by Yahoo access the Yahoo! Search APIs using pYsearch, an open-source Python library created by Leif Hedstrom. To use this library, developers can create a search query object, execute, and receive a results object as response. Download available at Sourceforge http://sourceforge.net/projects/pysearch/
Description.208: In the BigOven Recipe site, users can find recipes, plan menus, and make grocery lists with the goal to facilitate mobile access from iPhone, iPad, Android, and Windows phone. The BigOven Recipe PHP library by Chris Pliakas access the API services of recipes, ingredients, and grocery lists. This library can be installed with composer, dependency manager for PHP at https://getcomposer.org/
Description.209: PushBullet can connect all devices to share files and receive notifications. It works officially with iOS and Android, and independently for Ubuntu, Blackberry, and Windows Phone. The PushBullet PHP library by Ivaylo Stoyanov allows to manage contacts, create/delete channels, and manage channel subscriptions. Available links to the official API, blogs, and apps.
Description.210: With PushBullet, users can stay connected in multiple devices at once. This allows to receive calls and notifications as well as send files and links. The PHP SDK for PushBullet contains instructions for usage and installation. PushBullet officially works with Mac and Windows and it can be accessed through Facebook or Gmail. Independently, PushBullet also works with Ubuntu, Blackberry, and Windows Phone.
Description.211: This Amazon EC2 Node.js library can access Amazon EC2 API and Product Advertising API, both part of Amazon Web Services. Amazon EC2 is about application development stored in a secure cloud. In this library, submitted by user mirkok5, developers can find usage, credentials, metadata API, IAM roles, and tests.
Description.212: The DocuSign Java library by DocuSign offers a Java REST API that consumes RESTful services related to electronic signature. The access to work with Java has the potential to automate signatures for contracts and documents. At the same time this project provides lines of code, it also displays a redirecting link to study demo services from the official site at http://iodocs.docusign.com/
Description.213: The official DocuSign .NET library integrates electronic signature into applications and websites. It's available through NuGet, a central package repository for Microsoft development. This project contains pre-requisites, which consist on a DocuSign developer account to obtain a key and a quick start guide, that explains how to add the DocuSign .NET client, how to authenticate with DocuSign, and how to create a DocuSign envelope. The link, Examples.cs, provide code samples for this project.
Description.214: The Testdroid Cloud Python Library by Bitbar allows developers to integrate version 2 of the Testdroid Cloud API into their Python applications.
Description.215: The Viki Ruby Library by Viki allows developers to integrate the Viki API's methods into their Ruby applications. This is an official gem for version 4 of the API.
Description.216: The Twitter Node.js Library by Tim Whitlock allows developers to integrate the Twitter and Twitter Streaming APIs into their Node.js applications. This library supports version 1.1 of both APIs.
Description.217: The BigCommerce Ruby Library by Christian Orthmann allows developers to integrate the BigCommerce API into their Ruby applications.
Description.218: The TwitchTV JavaScript library by Schmoopiie is a work in progress that aims to interact with the API access to TwitchTV user, channel, and team information. In this case, "twitch-tmi," as the developer refers to his project, is not affiliated to TwitchTV.
Description.219: The Dice Jobs PHP library by Karl Hughes is not affiliated with Dice.com, however it has the potential to work with the version 1 of the Dice Jobs API. The API allows to search for jobs, access jobs by ID number, and obtain lists of jobs. To be well informed in the technology job search process, Dice.com also provides tech insights. Developers should note that this library is a work in progress. They can contact author karl@packback.co
Description.220: The Google Plus JavaScript library by Google supports Chrome 8+, Firefox 3.5+, MSIE 8+, and Safari 4+ browsers. The aim of this library is to facilitate the JavaScript writing process that works with Google+ and other services such as Calendar and Analytics. For a complete list of the APIs that interact with this library, users can review the APIs explorer site https://developers.google.com/apis-explorer/#p/
Description.221: The Google Plus .NET library by Google includes a sample to build on top of the Google+ platform. With additional information shared on the site, users can browse .NET documentation for the Google+ API, read the developers' guide for the API, and interact with Google+ API in a browser. To install, developers need a NuGet package from the Google.Apis.plus.
Description.222: The Google Distance Matrix API displays travel distance and time of various origins and destinations. This is the Google Distance Matrix Node.js library developed by Ecil Teodoro. Contains parameters to use API key and client & signature. The different factors of this Node.js module are the recognition of multiple origins and the data returned by the Google API.
Description.223: The Google Distance Matrix Go Library by Jon Dunning affords to get the distance and travel times between various origins and destinations. It handles Google API rate limiting and URL length. Available installation, usage, and limitations. Supports driving, walking, and bicycling modes.
Description.224: Goodreads.com API affords to get books on a shelf, get members' updates, and get reviews by ISBN. The Goodreads.com C# library created by Jason Kulatunga includes client example, installation, and API reference. The author uses it to authenticate and integrate with QuietThyme.com. For more information, contact jason@thesparktree.com
Description.225: A Fitbit Node.js library by developer Guo Yu is available on Npm and Github. It contains simple code lines to install and links with API instructions from the official site to clarify any doubts. The Fitbit API affords to read and write methods to support health and fitness applications. For more info, contact author i@guoyu.me
Description.226: This is a .NET library for the Fitbit API developed by Aaron Coleman. Besides the library, the project contains NUnit tests, NUnit integration within the API, and a sample to use. Fitbit tracks patterns of health and fitness practices using mobile devices. Currently, the author is working on an updated version at https://github.com/aarondcoleman/Fitbit.NET/wiki/PREPARING-FOR-BREAKING-CHANGES---v2-Fitbit.NET-API-Library-In-Development
Description.227: Fitbit Node.js library by Lukas Olson. Available to make API calls to the Fitbit servers, once developers use consumerkey and consumersecret to get a request token. With the Fitbit API, users are able to track healthy practices from a mobile device using applications, products, and services related to fitness and health.
Description.228: The Twilio sms-rb Ruby Library by Pat Nakajima is a Ruby library to assist with sending text messages easily with the Twilio API. Twilio provides a simple hosted API and markup language for businesses to quickly build scalable, reliable and advanced voice and SMS communications applications.
Description.229: The Twilio-Rails Ruby Library by Hemant Bhanoo is a Ruby Rails Library for the Twilio API. This library and it's code helps make develop Twilio applications easier in rails. Twilio provides a simple hosted API and markup language for businesses to quickly build scalable, reliable and advanced voice and SMS communications applications.
Description.230: The Twilio Ruby Wrapper by Webficient is a Ruby Gem wrapper for the Twilio REST API. It also acts as a response handler for the Twilio Markup XML. Twilio provides a simple hosted API and markup language for businesses to quickly build scalable, reliable and advanced voice and SMS communications applications.
Description.231: The Fuel-Twilio PHP Library by Matthew McConnell is a PHP community supported library for the Twilio API. It is a Twilio plugin for Fuel PHP, and is a package to allow service with the Twilio services. Twilio provides a simple hosted API and markup language for businesses to quickly build scalable, reliable and advanced voice and SMS communications applications.
Description.232: The official Google Picasa client libraries help to write applications with the Picasa Web Albums Data API. Users can upload and share photos on Google+, tag friends, and filter images. Picasa is available for download.
Description.233: This Java library is an updated version of the original ga.js analytics library. Insert this Java code snippet into your website's page templates to begin tracking how users interact with your website. The basic analytics.js library will record pageviews for your site. See the project doucmentation for information on tracking more complex or additional metrics.
Description.234: The Geocode Node.js library by Nicolas Chaulet can geocode and reverse geocode with the providers of Google Geocoding, FreegeoipGeocoder, DataScienceToolkitGeocoder, OpenStreetMapGeocoder, MapQuestGeocoder, Open MapQuestGeocoder, ArcGis Online Geocoding, TomTomGeocoder, OpenCage Geocoder, Smarty street geocoder, and Geocodio.
Description.235: This PHP library aims to be the most functional geo-aware tool because it includes the providers of ArcGISOnline, GeoIP2, Google Maps, GoogleMapsBusiness, MaxMindBinary, Nominatim, TomTom, and Yandex. What this library provides is powerful abstraction layer for geocoding manipulations, according to the author. A complete guide to use the PHP library is available on William Durand's GitHub site.
Description.236: Google offers a number of libraries in Python language to use Google App Engine, the platform-as-a-service that allows to build apps in the cloud. It is allowed to add third party packages to the application. Python documentation available at https://cloud.google.com/appengine/docs/python/refdocs/
Description.237: The Associated Press Ruby library loads election data from the AP into MySQL. This code has been used by The Huffington Post since the 2012 with the main goal to obtain fast results of the AP's FTP server and into MySQL. The author clarifies that this repository is not affiliated with the AP. Developers should have a contract with AP and an account on the FTP server to use the code. Jay Boice authored in 2014.
Description.238: This ESHA Nutrition Ruby library developed by Jens Balvig aims to work easily with the ESHA nutrition API. Offers code for installation and usage. ESHA nutrition is a food labeling software that affords to search foods with nutrients and calorie count. ESHA products include R&D, food processor, database licensing, and web services.
Description.239: The VIES VAT Node.js library by Bill Gao shows examples and returns with valid and invalid responses. The goal is to call the Web Service offered by VIES(VAT information exchange system) for VAT (values added tax) number verification purposes. For more detail, users can contact the author viruschidai@gmail.com
Description.240: This FatSecret Python library aims to facilitate data visualization accessed from the API. It includes categorized methods such as foods, recipes, recipe types, saved meals, exercises, profile management, food diary, exercise diary, and weight diary.
Description.241: The FatSecret iOS library by Parker Wightman was designed keeping the FatSecret API in mind. With instructions for installation and usage, this library offers Food Search and Get Food as the main code libraries for iOS. FatSecret API has the capacity to access food, nutrition, and recipe databases with the goal to improve the development of mobile apps.
Description.242: This is an Android wrapper library for the Google Places API created by Greg Marzouka. It can interact with the API functions of reference, localization, and mapping. It could be useful to create location awareness, search everywhere, and autocomplete as stated on the official Google Places API site. This site provides a link to display a showcase to discover Google Places API implementation. Author Greg Marzouka is on Twitter @gregmarzouka
Description.243: The Google Places iOS library by Lukas Kukacka uses a simple block interface to interact with the features of the API that include mapping, localization, and reference. This project offers place search, with nearby search and text search. It also provides places details, with a more detailed information about a specific location. Available as CocoaPods.
Description.244: The official Demandware Python library supports the goals of e-commerce, IT infrastructure management, and strategic growth of the Open Commerce API. The interaction with the API allows developers to create unique shopping experiences using outside web functionalities. The library was built with Sphinx, a Python documentation generator, and shared on ReadtheDocs. Developers can edit on GitHub.
Description.245: This is a .NET instant answer library written in C# for the DuckDuckGo Instant Answer API. It was created by Tim Kelly. DuckDuckGo is a search engine that aims to protect the privacy of users who enter personal queries. It does not track users' behavior. DuckDuckGo's RESTful API displays responses in JSON and XML.
Description.246: The Del.icio.us Java library by David Czarnecki was created years ago to interact with del.icio.us API. What this service does is to bookmark favorite websites that can later be accessed online from anywhere. The RESTful API works via HTTP and returns XML responses. For any updates, contact the author me@davidczarnecki.com
Description.247: The MyFitnessPal Go project by Matt Ho includes a library with food diary. Useful to retrieve macro intake for today and retrieve macro intake for a specific date. MyFitnessPal is an application that tracks the progress of users who are committed to changes in diet and exercise. The API is private and available on the MyFitnessPal site.
Description.248: This is a Ruby wrapper for the Groupon API. It features activities to do in major cities. To use this library, developers need a key. Next, they can access 'listing divisions,' 'finding deals,' and 'finding deals by division.' Stephen St. Martin authored on GitHub. Copyrighted by Wynn Netherland.
Description.249: The Groupon Java Library by Jessica Chung interacts with the API, that allows to build Groupon applications. Developers can improve, add extensions, and create multiple platform interfaces considering groups of clients who want to find the best deals nearby. Groupon official site offers an API developer forum.
